       "<h1 id=\"deep-learning-models-practical-exam-survival-guide\">Deep\n",
       "Learning Models — Practical Exam Survival Guide</h1>\n",
       "<blockquote>\n",
       "<p><strong>How to use this document:</strong> Read it end-to-end once.\n",
       "Then re-read only the chapter you draw in the chit. Every chapter is\n",
       "self-contained — opener, theory, code walk, FAQs, viva bank, keywords,\n",
       "what-to-draw, applications/advantages/limitations.</p>\n",
       "</blockquote>\n",
       "<hr />\n",
       "<h2 id=\"exam-playbook-read-first-5-min\">0. Exam playbook (read first — 5\n",
       "min)</h2>\n",
       "<p><strong>Word on the street (yesterday’s batch):</strong></p>\n",
       "<ul>\n",
       "<li>No kinky surprises — <strong>only what was done in\n",
       "labs</strong>.</li>\n",
       "<li><strong>Pick your own dataset</strong> — don’t be forced into an\n",
       "unfamiliar one.</li>\n",
       "<li>Hardest spots to draw: <strong>GAN / pretrained model</strong> —\n",
       "both covered in detail here.</li>\n",
       "<li><strong>She sometimes makes you write the architecture and theory by\n",
       "hand</strong> — memorise layer stacks (see the drawing section).</li>\n",
       "<li>Yogita Hande examiner → calm, fair.</li>\n",
       "<li>Copy allowed sort-of; Wi-Fi password helps — but this guide is\n",
       "offline-complete.</li>\n",
       "</ul>\n",
       "<p><strong>Rules of thumb during viva:</strong></p>\n",
       "<ol type=\"1\">\n",
       "<li><strong>Start every topic with one crisp sentence</strong> (“CNN is\n",
       "a neural network that uses convolutional layers to learn spatial\n",
       "features from images”).</li>\n",
       "<li><strong>Drop keywords early</strong> — examiner hears them and ticks\n",
       "the box.</li>\n",
       "<li>If you don’t know, say “I remember the intuition but not the exact\n",
       "formula” — partial credit, not a lie.</li>\n",
       "<li><strong>Always tie concept → example.</strong> “Sigmoid is used in\n",
       "binary classification output, e.g., spam/not-spam.”</li>\n",
       "<li>When pointing at code: name the <strong>function</strong>, the\n",
       "<strong>argument</strong>, and the <strong>why</strong>.</li>\n",
       "</ol>\n",
       "<p><strong>The 7 assignments (in order drawn on the chit):</strong></p>\n",
       "<ol type=\"1\">\n",
       "<li>Installation and study of TensorFlow</li>\n",
       "<li>Basic fundamental operations using tensors</li>\n",
       "<li>Implement Simple Neural Network using Python</li>\n",
       "<li>Implement a Convolution Neural Network (CNN) architecture</li>\n",
       "<li>Implement a Deep Sequence Model (RNN / LSTM)</li>\n",
       "<li>Implement a GAN</li>\n",
       "<li>Implement a Pretrained model</li>\n",
       "</ol>\n",
